  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks designed to combat money laundering at national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National Legislation:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (United States)\n- Money Laundering Control Act\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n\n3. Key Compliance Measures:\n- Mandatory customer identification\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Regular financial audits\n- Enhanced due diligence for high-risk transactions\n\n4. Penalties:\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Significant financial penalties\n- Asset seizure\n- Business license revocation\n\n5. Regulatory Bodies:\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Central banks\n- Law enforcement agencies\n- Regulatory compliance departments\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities across different sectors and jurisdictions.",
